The Herald Prosper Ndlovu in Dubai, UAE ENVIRONMENT, Climate, Tourism and Hospitality Deputy Minister Barbara Rwodzi, has arrived in Dubai, United Arab Emirates, ahead of the tourism and travel conference to be hosted by the country here on Saturday and Sunday. She has been welcomed to the Zimbabwe Pavilion by the country’s expo Commissioner General, Ambassador Mary Mubi, who is taking her through a tour of various exhibits. Zimbabwe is keen to penetrate the Middle East and Asian markets and the forthcoming indaba would thrive to market the country’ rich tourism on offer to this target destination.